{ Chessable member Rebse mentioned this fine combination by him. It's nice to see readers successfully apply tactical ideas from the course. }
1. Bxh7+ Kxh7 2. Qh5+ Kg8 3. Bxg7
{ Excellent! And the only way to win. Else, Black would be able to organize a defense with Bd3-g6. }
3... Kxg7 4. Qh6+ Kg8 5. g6
{ White won after the most precise   18...fxg6  19.Qxg6+  Kh8  20.Qh6+  Kg8  21.Rg1+  Bg5  22.Qg6+  Kh8  23.Rxg5  +-  with mate to follow.   18.Rg1  with the idea Rg4-h4 is good, too. }
*

