{ In a similar manner to the typical Sicilian exchange sacrifice on c3, if Black has castled short and has to take back with the g-pawn, this exchange sacrifice is basically always correct. Here, White has several ways to reinforce his attack, e.g.   20...gxf6  21.Qxh6  Rxb1  22.Nxb1  fxe5  23.Qg5+  Kh8  24.Qh5+  Kg8  25.exd5  +-  followed by Bxe5. }
